rough country
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:land that is difficult to access easily, to muster, manage and graze [ with a low carrying-capacity and often with growth of weeds and scrub.]


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
